headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 20 of his 41 points in the fourth quarter and the Minnesota Timberwolves overcome a sloppy first half and beat the NBA-worst Washington Wizards 120-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 41 as the Timberwolves beat struggling Wizards 120-106

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 36 points, Malik Beasley had 22 and a pair of clutch 3-pointers in the final 40 seconds and the surging Detroit Pistons beat New York 124-119 on Monday night, their second straight victory over the Knicks after dropping the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham scores 36 points and the surging Pistons beat the Knicks again, 124-119

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Ochai Agbaji scored the go-ahead basket with 1:33 left in the fourth quarter and the Toronto Raptors rallied to beat the Golden State Warriors 104-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Agbaji and Barnes lead the Raptors to a 104-101 win over the Warriors

headlines.description: — Jalen Green tied his career high with 42 points, capped by a layup that gave Houston the lead late, and the Rockets rallied for a 120-118 win over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green ties career high with 42 points as Rockets rally for 120-118 victory over Grizzlies

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 23 points and eight rebounds, Harrison Barnes scored 10 of his 17 points in the fourth quarter, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Lakers 126-102 on Monday night in Los Angeles' first game back from two postponements due to the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers lose to Spurs 126-102 in their 1st game back after wildfire postponements

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 13 of his 26 points in a third-quarter revival that rallied the Los Angeles Clippers past the Miami Heat 109-98 on Monday night, snapping a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden's big 3rd quarter helps Clippers rally past Heat 109-98
